Additionally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on the CIFAR-10 dataset, which is a popular benchmark dataset in the machine learning community. 

The paper could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as the experiments are conducted on image classification tasks. 

Furthermore, the paper involves adversarial robustness, which is a topic of interest in the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

The paper also deals with security and robustness, which are topics of interest in the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). 

Finally, the paper involves neural networks, which are a topic of interest in the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
